contentrichtext.text: {{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox protected area of Australia | name = Forbes Islands National Park | iucn_category = II | image = | caption = | locator_x = | locator_y = | nearest_town_or_city = | coordinates = {{Coord|12|17|10|S|143|24|40|E|type:landmark_region:AU-QLD|display=inline,title}} | area = {{Convert|1.09|km2|sqmi|2|abbr=on}} | established = 1990 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | managing_authorities = [[Queensland Parks and Wildlife Service]] | official_site = }} '''Forbes Islands''' is a national park in [[Queensland]], [[Australia]], 1,962 km northwest of [[Brisbane]] in the [[Great Barrier Reef Marine Park]] [[Queensland]] and is located about 40 km North East of [[Iron Range National Park]] and [[Lockhart River, Queensland|Lockhart River]] in the [[Cape Weymouth]] area in the [[Coral Sea]] just off the small locality of Portland Roads. ==See also== {{Portal|Queensland}} * [[Protected areas of Queensland]] {{National Parks of Queensland}} [[Category:National parks of Far North Queensland]] [[Category:Islands of Queensland]] [[Category:Protected areas established in 1990]] {{Queensland-national-park-stub}}
